<p class="p0 c21"><span class="c16">③</span><span class="c20"> 《论语》有<span class="c18">“</span><span class="c19">君子笃于亲则民兴于仁</span><span class="c18">”</span><span class="c19">，如果仅仅是做做样子而让百姓去效法，而没有</span><span class="c18">“</span><span class="c19">循理因资</span><span class="c18">”</span><span class="c19">，这样的</span><span class="c18">“</span><span class="c19">无为</span><span class="c18">”</span><span class="c19">则近于儒家。</span></span><span class="c20"></span></p>
<p class="p0 c21"><span class="c16">④</span><span class="c20"> 无为第一义是无私，无为第二义是无执。老子的<span class="c18">“</span><span class="c19">无为</span><span class="c18">”</span><span class="c19">，实是积极遵道而行。第二，</span><span class="c18">“</span><span class="c19">无为也则用天下而有余</span><span class="c18">”</span><span class="c19">。第三，在政治上要循理和不扰。第四，掌握法则能预见未来。第五，人民顺风而化，不需法律。见詹剑锋《老子其人其书及其道论》，华中师范大学出版社</span><span class="c18">2006</span><span class="c19">年</span><span class="c18">3</span><span class="c19">月版，第</span><span class="c18">290</span><span class="c19">页。</span></span><span class="c20"></span></p>
